June 26: Initial conditions

Emma Holmes

6/25/2020

Initial conditions in the stock model

## Set initial conditions
lambda_init <-0.9
omega_init <-  0.9
debt_share_init <-0.2
a_init <- 1

IC <- c(
  K       =  lambda_init * Parms[['nu']] * a_init,
  w       =  omega_init * a_init,
  p       =  1,
  debt    =  debt_share_init * lambda_init * a_init,
  a       =  a_init,
  pop     =  1,
  g_sigma =  -0.0105,  # Growth rate of the emissions intensity of the economy
  n       =  0, #0.03,     # Emissions reduction rate
  E_ind   =  35.85,    # Industrial CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  CO2_AT  =  851,      # CO2-e concentration in the atmosphere layer, in Gt C
  CO2_UP  =  460,      # CO2-e concentration in the biosphere and upper ocean layer, in Gt C
  CO2_LO  =  1740,     # CO2-e concentration in the deep ocean layer, in Gt C
  E_land  =  2.6,      # Exogenous land use change CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  p_BS    =  547.22,   # Backstop technology price level
  Temp    =  0.85,     # Temperature in the atmosphere, biosphere, and upper ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
  Temp_LO =  0.0068    # Temperature in the deep ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
)

#=================================================================================
# Set up simulation
Time <- c(
  start         =     2020, 
  end           =     2120,
  step          =     0.05
)

Options <- list(
  invest = 'exp',  # exp / arctan / lin
  damage_scenario = 'None',
  p_carb_scheme = 'Low',
  subsidy = 0   # fraction of abatement costs subsidized by government
)

IC[['n']] = 0.03
Parms[['carbon_slope']] = 0.1
#================================================================================
Sim <- simulation(time       = Time,
                        init_state = IC,
                        parms      = Parms,
                        method     = 'rk4')

Because the carbon price is set according to the environmental parameters, the economic initial conditions need to balance with this (i.e. can’t have an initial carbon price of $20 if the GDP is initially). I’m not quite sure which initial conditions to choose, but if I choose \(a=100\) instead of \(a=1\) as before, the stock model behaves as expected for good initial conditions.

AFD initial conditions

IC.AFD <- c(
  ### Separated
  # North
  Y_N       =  30,       # global GDP, in trillions of USD
  d_N       =  1.5328,   # private debt ratio of the economy
  lambda_N  =  0.6748,   # employment rate of the global economy
  omega_N   =  0.5782,   # wage share of the economy
  N_N       =  4.8255,   # Workforce of the (world) economy, in billions
  g_sigma_N =  -0.0105,  # Growth rate of the emissions intensity of the economy
  n_N       =  0.03,     # Emissions reduction rate
  E_ind_N   =  35.85,   # Industrial CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e

  # Unique
  CO2_AT   =  851,      # CO2-e concentration in the atmosphere layer, in Gt C
  CO2_UP   =  460,      # CO2-e concentration in the biosphere and upper ocean layer, in Gt C
  CO2_LO   =  1740,     # CO2-e concentration in the deep ocean layer, in Gt C
  E_land   =  2.6,      # Exogenous land use change CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  p        =  1,        # Composite good price level
  p_BS     =  547.22,   # Backstop technology price level
  Temp     =  0.85,     # Temperature in the atmosphere, biosphere, and upper ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
  Temp_LO  =  0.0068    # Temperature in the deep ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
)

a.AFD <- IC.AFD[['Y_N']] / (IC.AFD[['lambda_N']] * IC.AFD[['N_N']])
Debt.AFD <- IC.AFD[['d_N']] * IC.AFD[['p']] * IC.AFD[['Y_N']]
w.AFD <- IC.AFD[['omega_N']] * IC.AFD[['p']] * a.AFD

IC_og <- c(
  K       =  IC.AFD[['Y_N']] * Parms[['nu']],
  w       =  w.AFD,
  p       =  1,
  debt    = Debt.AFD,
  a       = a.AFD,
  pop     = IC.AFD[['N_N']],
  g_sigma =  -0.0105,  # Growth rate of the emissions intensity of the economy
  n       =  0.03,     # Emissions reduction rate
  E_ind   =  35.85,    # Industrial CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  CO2_AT  =  851,      # CO2-e concentration in the atmosphere layer, in Gt C
  CO2_UP  =  460,      # CO2-e concentration in the biosphere and upper ocean layer, in Gt C
  CO2_LO  =  1740,     # CO2-e concentration in the deep ocean layer, in Gt C
  E_land  =  2.6,      # Exogenous land use change CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  p_BS    =  547.22,   # Backstop technology price level
  Temp    =  0.85,     # Temperature in the atmosphere, biosphere, and upper ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
  Temp_LO =  0.0068    # Temperature in the deep ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
)

IC_rd <- c(
  lambda = IC.AFD[['lambda_N']],
  omega = IC.AFD[['omega_N']], 
  debt_share = IC.AFD[['d_N']],
  p   = 1,
  K       =  IC.AFD[['Y_N']] * Parms[['nu']],
  g_sigma =  -0.0105,  # Growth rate of the emissions intensity of the economy
  n       =  0.03,     # Emissions reduction rate
  E_ind   =  35.85,    # Industrial CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  CO2_AT  =  851,      # CO2-e concentration in the atmosphere layer, in Gt C
  CO2_UP  =  460,      # CO2-e concentration in the biosphere and upper ocean layer, in Gt C
  CO2_LO  =  1740,     # CO2-e concentration in the deep ocean layer, in Gt C
  E_land  =  2.6,      # Exogenous land use change CO2-e emissions, in Gt CO2-e
  p_BS    =  547.22,   # Backstop technology price level
  Temp    =  0.85,     # Temperature in the atmosphere, biosphere, and upper ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
  Temp_LO =  0.0068    # Temperature in the deep ocean layer, in degrees Celsius
)
